<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="435" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1435,221,625]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,221,244]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">Description.</emphasis>
Body length (including forewing): ♂, 
<quantity box="[704,790,221,244]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" unit="mm" value="6.7">6.7 mm</quantity>
. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[887,1008,221,244]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,204,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1412,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Pythamus rufus sp. nov.: 11. male habitus, dorsal view; 12. male habitus, lateral view; 13. male head, dorsal view; 14. male face; 15. subgenital plate, ventral view; 16. aedeagus, lateral view; 17. aedeagus, ventral view; 18. male genital capsule, lateral view; 19. connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235242/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">Figs 11, 13</figureCitation>
) with red markings at lateral carina and submarginal carina. Median longitudinal carina of frontoclypeus is lamellate in upper half (
<figureCitation box="[1128,1251,256,279]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,204,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1412,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Pythamus rufus sp. nov.: 11. male habitus, dorsal view; 12. male habitus, lateral view; 13. male head, dorsal view; 14. male face; 15. subgenital plate, ventral view; 16. aedeagus, lateral view; 17. aedeagus, ventral view; 18. male genital capsule, lateral view; 19. connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235242/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">Figs 12, 13</figureCitation>
). Forewing (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,204,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1412,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Pythamus rufus sp. nov.: 11. male habitus, dorsal view; 12. male habitus, lateral view; 13. male head, dorsal view; 14. male face; 15. subgenital plate, ventral view; 16. aedeagus, lateral view; 17. aedeagus, ventral view; 18. male genital capsule, lateral view; 19. connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235242/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">Figs 11, 12</figureCitation>
) brown and translucent, marked with dark chocolate brown stripes in middle and end part, and two white semicircular spots on outer and inner margins respectively.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1435,221,625]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
Male pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[364,444,360,383]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,204,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1412,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Pythamus rufus sp. nov.: 11. male habitus, dorsal view; 12. male habitus, lateral view; 13. male head, dorsal view; 14. male face; 15. subgenital plate, ventral view; 16. aedeagus, lateral view; 17. aedeagus, ventral view; 18. male genital capsule, lateral view; 19. connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235242/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
Fig. 
<number box="[417,444,360,383]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) posteriorly narrowed along with caudo-ventral margin. Pygofer ventral process (
<figureCitation box="[1347,1427,360,383]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,204,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1412,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Pythamus rufus sp. nov.: 11. male habitus, dorsal view; 12. male habitus, lateral view; 13. male head, dorsal view; 14. male face; 15. subgenital plate, ventral view; 16. aedeagus, lateral view; 17. aedeagus, ventral view; 18. male genital capsule, lateral view; 19. connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235242/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
Fig. 
<number box="[1400,1427,360,383]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) rather straight, slightly longer than pygofer, with about 
<number box="[752,765,394,417]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" value="5.0">5</number>
toothed process distally. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1284,394,417]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,204,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1412,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Pythamus rufus sp. nov.: 11. male habitus, dorsal view; 12. male habitus, lateral view; 13. male head, dorsal view; 14. male face; 15. subgenital plate, ventral view; 16. aedeagus, lateral view; 17. aedeagus, ventral view; 18. male genital capsule, lateral view; 19. connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235242/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">Figs 16, 17</figureCitation>
) with bilobed apodeme arising from atrium and extended dorsolaterad; shaft recurved dorsally, apex hooked, subapex with a pair of lateral conical processes; gonopore apical. Style (
<figureCitation box="[673,751,464,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,204,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1412,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Pythamus rufus sp. nov.: 11. male habitus, dorsal view; 12. male habitus, lateral view; 13. male head, dorsal view; 14. male face; 15. subgenital plate, ventral view; 16. aedeagus, lateral view; 17. aedeagus, ventral view; 18. male genital capsule, lateral view; 19. connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235242/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
Fig. 
<number box="[722,751,464,487]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
), with footlike apex of apophysis having elongated lateral angle, apodeme apex acute. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[567,644,498,521]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,204,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1412,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Pythamus rufus sp. nov.: 11. male habitus, dorsal view; 12. male habitus, lateral view; 13. male head, dorsal view; 14. male face; 15. subgenital plate, ventral view; 16. aedeagus, lateral view; 17. aedeagus, ventral view; 18. male genital capsule, lateral view; 19. connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235242/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
Fig. 
<number box="[617,644,498,521]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
) elongate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
